bfFS — Filesystem-to-Brainfuck Compiler
todotodotosotodotoeot
A TODO-oriented README with Virtual Linux Direction

---

🧠 Concept

bfFS is a compiler that transforms a structured filesystem into a Brainfuck program.

Instead of writing code in text files, programs are defined by:

- file names
- file extensions
- directory structure
- traversal order

The filesystem itself becomes the source code.

---

🎯 Expanded Goal

Build a full pipeline that enables a virtual Linux-like environment running inside Brainfuck.

Filesystem → IR → Bytecode → Brainfuck VM → Virtual OS

This project is not about compiling the Linux kernel directly.
It is about reconstructing a minimal OS environment inside a Brainfuck-based virtual machine.

---

🧱 System Architecture

[ bfFS Filesystem ]
        ↓
[ Compiler ]
        ↓
[ Intermediate Representation (IR) ]
        ↓
[ Bytecode პროგრამs / Disk Image ]
        ↓
[ Brainfuck Virtual Machine ]
        ↓
[ Minimal Linux-like Environment ]

---

🔑 Core Idea

Brainfuck is not the OS.

👉 Brainfuck is the hardware emulator

Inside it, we implement:

- a virtual CPU
- memory
- syscalls
- a filesystem
- a shell

---

⚙️ Brainfuck Virtual Machine (Planned)

Components

1. Virtual CPU

- [ ] Registers (R0–Rn)
- [ ] Instruction Pointer (IP)
- [ ] Stack Pointer (SP)

2. Instruction Set (Bytecode)

Example (draft):

01 → LOAD
02 → STORE
03 → ADD
04 → JMP
05 → JZ (jump if zero)
06 → SYSCALL

---

3. Execution Loop

while true:
  opcode = memory[IP]
  execute(opcode)
  IP++

Implemented entirely in Brainfuck.

---

4. Memory Layout

[ Registers ][ Program ][ Heap ][ Stack ][ I/O ]

---

🧩 Virtual OS Layer

A minimal Linux-like abstraction layer implemented inside the VM.

Syscalls (Planned)

ID| Function
0| write
1| read
2| open (virtual)
3| exit

---

Features

- [ ] Command loop (shell)
- [ ] Program loading from memory
- [ ] File abstraction
- [ ] Process simulation (cooperative multitasking)

---

📁 bfFS as Virtual Disk

The bfFS structure doubles as a disk image:

bfFS → parsed → loaded into VM memory

- Directories → filesystem hierarchy
- Files → program/data blobs
- Extensions → instructions or metadata

---

📁 Filesystem Specification (Compiler Input)

File Naming

0001_init.bf+
0002_move.ptrr
0003_loop.loop/

---

Extension → Brainfuck Mapping (MVP)

Extension| Brainfuck
".bf+"| "+"
".bf-"| "-"
".ptrr"| ">"
".ptrl"| "<"
".out"| "."
".in"| ","
".loop"| "["
".end"| "]"

---

Directory Semantics

Directory Type| Meaning
"*.loop/"| Begin loop block "["
"*.end/"| End loop block "]"
other dirs| Nested execution scope

---

Traversal Rules

- Depth-first
- Lexicographically sorted
- Deterministic output

---

⚙️ Compiler Pipeline

[ Filesystem ]
      ↓
[ Parser ]
      ↓
[ IR ]
      ↓
[ Bytecode Generator ]
      ↓
[ Brainfuck Emitter ]

